The use of polynomial-time solutions and approximations also suggests it may belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category. The paper also involves optimization and complexity analysis, which suggests it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) categories.
